1
00:00:00,834 --> 00:00:02,044
(MOUSE SQUEAKS)

2
00:00:02,169 --> 00:00:03,420
(PENGUINS CHIRP)

3
00:00:05,714 --> 00:00:07,132
(ALL CHEERING)

4
00:00:10,135 --> 00:00:11,303
(SCREECHES)

5
00:00:12,888 --> 00:00:14,014
Adventure Time

6
00:00:14,056 --> 00:00:15,516
Come on, grab your friends

7
00:00:15,557 --> 00:00:18,143
We'll go to very distant lands

8
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:20,395
With Jake the dog
and Finn the human

9
00:00:20,479 --> 00:00:22,022
The fun will never end

10
00:00:22,147 --> 00:00:24,149
It's Adventure Time

11
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:35,077
BEEMO: Football, you don't mean that.

12
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:36,453
FOOTBALL: I do, Beemo.

13
00:00:36,578 --> 00:00:38,413
I don't say things I don't mean.

14
00:00:38,830 --> 00:00:41,416
You look very smart
and very handsome today.

15
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:44,461
Oh, Football, thank you.

16
00:00:44,586 --> 00:00:46,463
I love you so much.

17
00:00:46,547 --> 00:00:47,839
I love you, Beemo.

18
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:51,677
Ring, ring. Hello? Football?
This is Beemo.

19
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:52,970
Oh, hello, Beemo.

20
00:00:53,095 --> 00:00:55,430
What a wonderful surprise. What's up?

21
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:56,848
Oh, nothing.

22
00:00:56,974 --> 00:00:59,184
Just wanted to say that I love you.

23
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:01,478
I love you, too. Goodbye. Click.

24
00:01:02,854 --> 00:01:04,815
Can I tell you a secret?

25
00:01:05,148 --> 00:01:07,568
Of course, Beemo.
You can tell me anything.

26
00:01:08,694 --> 00:01:09,945
I love you.

27
00:01:09,945 --> 00:01:11,697
Oh! (GIGGLES)

28
00:01:13,282 --> 00:01:15,284
Now you tell me a secret, Football.

29
00:01:17,661 --> 00:01:21,081
I wish I could spend just one day
on the other side of the mirror.

30
00:01:21,957 --> 00:01:25,085
Well, let's switch places for the day.

31
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:27,421
Oh, Beemo, you'd do that for me?

32
00:01:27,713 --> 00:01:30,716
Yes, Football. Because I love you.

33
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:32,467
Oh, Beemo.

34
00:01:36,847 --> 00:01:38,432
(GRUNTING)

35
00:01:42,811 --> 00:01:43,979
(GROANING)

36
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,815
(PANTING)

37
00:01:47,858 --> 00:01:49,192
Oh! (LAUGHS)

38
00:01:49,985 --> 00:01:52,070
See you back here tomorrow, Football.

39
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:55,115
(GASPS)

40
00:01:56,825 --> 00:01:58,452
Oh! Oh!

41
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:01,079
Ah! Whoo.

42
00:02:02,372 --> 00:02:03,957
(MOANING, BUZZING)

43
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:14,801
Hello. My name is Football.

44
00:02:15,052 --> 00:02:19,431
And you are Carlos,
my best friend since college.

45
00:02:19,556 --> 00:02:20,891
(QUACKS)

46
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:24,311
Carlos.

47
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:25,812
(CHUCKLES)

48
00:02:25,896 --> 00:02:29,191
Okay, let's not leave it
so long next time, Carlos.

49
00:02:30,067 --> 00:02:31,193
(QUACKS)

50
00:02:32,069 --> 00:02:33,570
(LAUGHS)

51
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,201
Hmm?

52
00:02:40,410 --> 00:02:42,537
Jake, get out of my fruit, man!

53
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:45,040
- (LAUGHS)
- You're cute, but you're dirty.

54
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,333
- (CHUCKLES)
- (FOOTBALL GASPS)

55
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,210
(EXCLAIMING)

56
00:02:49,961 --> 00:02:52,547
Ooh. Ah!

57
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:55,217
What are you doing on the floor,
you bad baby?

58
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:59,721
Yes. Shh. Yes. I understand.

59
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:02,808
Oh, baby, don't turn around.

60
00:03:03,225 --> 00:03:04,810
But Finn is set right over there.

61
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:15,737
Hello, my name is Football.

62
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:18,240
Very nice to meet you, Football.

63
00:03:18,323 --> 00:03:20,200
How'd you get the name Football, Football?

64
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:23,245
- Beemo gave it to me.
- Is Beemo your little papa?

65
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:24,830
(GIGGLES)

66
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:30,252
Uh, so where do you live, Football?

67
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:32,838
- The mirror.
- Oh, yeah?

68
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:34,256
What's it like there?

69
00:03:34,965 --> 00:03:35,966
Cold.

70
00:03:36,591 --> 00:03:37,759
Empty.

71
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:39,636
It's... Lonely.

72
00:03:55,110 --> 00:03:56,153
Weird.

73
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,413
Very weird.

74
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,375
(DOOR CREAKS)

75
00:04:11,376 --> 00:04:12,544
Hello?

76
00:04:15,756 --> 00:04:18,759
Football, are you okay?
It's weird in here.

77
00:04:19,134 --> 00:04:20,594
I'm not going back, Beemo.

78
00:04:21,011 --> 00:04:23,388
Come closer, Football.
I can't hear you.

79
00:04:24,014 --> 00:04:28,018
I'm not going back, Beemo.
I'm staying on this side. Forever.

80
00:04:28,727 --> 00:04:30,645
Football. Football!

81
00:04:31,021 --> 00:04:34,024
No! No! Football, no!

82
00:04:37,152 --> 00:04:38,862
- (GRUNTS)
- (GRUNTS) Hyah!

83
00:04:38,904 --> 00:04:40,113
Yes!

84
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:42,282
Send another g-fruit to the slaughter, Jake!

85
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,159
- JAKE: You got it.
- Myah!

86
00:04:44,284 --> 00:04:45,786
(PANTING) Family meeting!

87
00:04:46,161 --> 00:04:47,412
- Hmm?
- Hmm?

88
00:04:47,871 --> 00:04:49,039
- What's up, B... Oh!
- (THUD)

89
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:52,501
(CHUCKLES) Sorry, man.

90
00:04:52,542 --> 00:04:54,920
OVEN: Did somebody say
"Family meeting?"

91
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:58,006
- What's up, Beemo?
- No, I'm not Beemo.

92
00:04:58,298 --> 00:04:59,382
I'm Football.

93
00:04:59,424 --> 00:05:00,675
- Oh, yeah.
- Hi, Football.

94
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:02,177
Yes. Hello.

95
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:03,678
I'm here, and I am Football.

96
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:06,181
And I will always be Football.

97
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:10,685
Because, Beemo told me to tell you

98
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:13,563
that he has gone away forever.

99
00:05:13,897 --> 00:05:15,440
- (SOBBING) Beemo.
- (OVEN DINGS)

100
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:19,528
"Take my place, Football,"
is what he said.

101
00:05:19,945 --> 00:05:21,196
(CHOMPING)

102
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:23,573
It was such a hard decision for him to make.

103
00:05:23,657 --> 00:05:24,825
(SNIFFLES)

104
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:26,910
He says for you guys to treat her...

105
00:05:26,952 --> 00:05:28,328
I mean, me.

106
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:32,332
As nice as you treated him, Beemo.

107
00:05:34,584 --> 00:05:36,044
We all need to stay strong,

108
00:05:36,795 --> 00:05:40,340
so the best thing everyone
can do is forget about him.

109
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:44,427
Remember, if you guys miss Beemo,
I miss him more.

110
00:05:46,221 --> 00:05:48,723
- That's great, Beemo.
- Football.

111
00:05:48,807 --> 00:05:50,225
Oh, right. Football.

112
00:05:55,230 --> 00:05:56,231
(SIGHS)

113
00:05:57,732 --> 00:05:59,234
Hey, Football.

114
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:00,861
Grapefruit for your troubles?

115
00:06:03,572 --> 00:06:06,491
Uh... (CHUCKLES) Oh, boy! Thanks!

116
00:06:07,117 --> 00:06:09,119
- Life is great!
- Yeah?

117
00:06:09,744 --> 00:06:11,246
You sure you're doing okay, little pal?

118
00:06:11,955 --> 00:06:14,374
- Mmm-hmm.
- Listen, B... Football.

119
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:16,710
You seem like you might be feeling, uh,

120
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:20,630
a little donked up in your head
or your heart or both.

121
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:22,007
And that's okay.

122
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:24,759
Everybody feels some type of
soul nausea like that sometimes.

123
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:27,220
- BEEMO: Football.
- Beemo?

124
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:30,348
I know how to follow you, Football.

125
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:33,768
- How did you get in the spoon?
- I figured it out!

126
00:06:34,019 --> 00:06:35,770
I'm going to get you, Football!

127
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:37,397
Did all that make sense?

128
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:38,899
(SCREAMS)

129
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:44,029
Yeah.

130
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:46,781
(PANTING) Oh, my gosh!
Oh, my gosh! Oh, my gosh!

131
00:06:46,907 --> 00:06:49,034
- (PANTING)
- (BEEMO GROWLING)

132
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:51,661
I'm going to get you, Football!

133
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:52,787
Ahhh!

134
00:06:53,997 --> 00:06:55,665
Ha! (PANTING)

135
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:57,667
Ha-ha!

136
00:06:57,918 --> 00:07:00,545
This is the way it has to be... Mo.

137
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:02,923
(PANTING)

138
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:05,425
(GASPS)

139
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:06,635
Oh, my gosh!

140
00:07:07,177 --> 00:07:11,181
Football! Football! Football.

141
00:07:12,307 --> 00:07:13,433
I'm sorry, Beemo.

142
00:07:13,683 --> 00:07:14,935
(GROWLS)

143
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:17,062
- Football.
- (GLASS SHATTERING)

144
00:07:17,187 --> 00:07:18,271
BEEMO: Don't do it!

145
00:07:18,313 --> 00:07:20,440
(FOOTBALL GRUNTING, PANTING)

146
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:22,067
Argh!

147
00:07:22,943 --> 00:07:23,944
(YELLS)

148
00:07:26,196 --> 00:07:27,530
(PANTING)

149
00:07:30,075 --> 00:07:32,786
Beemo, what is going on in here?

150
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:35,580
- Beemo?
- (GROWLING)

151
00:07:35,705 --> 00:07:37,207
Beemo! Ahhh!

152
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:39,584
- Beemo, why?
- (YELLING)

153
00:07:39,834 --> 00:07:41,294
(HUMMING) Huh?

154
00:07:41,336 --> 00:07:42,963
- Ow.
- Ahhh!

155
00:07:44,589 --> 00:07:45,715
BEEMO: Football?

156
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,467
Football, I know it's you.

157
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:50,971
We are both walking backwards
holding shillelaghs.

158
00:07:52,055 --> 00:07:53,056
Football?

159
00:07:54,349 --> 00:07:55,350
(SCREAMS)

160
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:00,355
Uh...

161
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:01,439
(GROWLS)

162
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:04,192
I'm gonna get you, Football!

163
00:08:04,234 --> 00:08:05,986
- Ahhh!
- (THUD)

164
00:08:06,695 --> 00:08:07,821
Ah!

165
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:10,490
FINN: All right, hand over
the shillelagh, Beemo.

166
00:08:10,615 --> 00:08:11,616
FOOTBALL: No! No! No!

167
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:14,452
Hey, Jake, Beemo went all
hog wild in the bathroom.

168
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:16,204
JAKE: Gross!

169
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:18,707
- Not like that.
- Ohhh!

170
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,585
Why you gonna be
so destructive today, Beemo?

171
00:08:23,086 --> 00:08:24,754
Are you doing robot puberty or something?

172
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,758
Jake! Jake, help me! Jake!

173
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:30,218
(SIGHS)

174
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:32,220
All right, Football, you know what time it is.

175
00:08:42,689 --> 00:08:46,693
Sooner or later, you're going to
slip on some spaghetti,

176
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:49,696
and I will be waiting on that shiny floor

177
00:08:49,821 --> 00:08:52,198
to drag you into your worst nightmare.

178
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:54,409
Beemo, you've seen where I live.

179
00:08:54,451 --> 00:08:56,036
You know why I don't want to go back.

180
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:57,579
But we made a deal,

181
00:08:57,704 --> 00:08:59,956
and where I come from, a factory,

182
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:03,209
breaking deals means
you have to go to the dirt hole.

183
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:07,964
That's where you are going, Football,
if you don't switch places with me.

184
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:09,090
No!

185
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:11,342
You're going to the dirt hole, Football.

186
00:09:11,426 --> 00:09:13,720
- Dirt hole!
- No!

187
00:09:14,596 --> 00:09:16,556
I'm going where you will never find me.

188
00:09:18,975 --> 00:09:20,560
JAKE: Aw, Football!

189
00:09:20,977 --> 00:09:23,730
FINN: Football! Beemo?

190
00:09:25,482 --> 00:09:26,858
(GRUNTING)

191
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:28,318
(PANTING)

192
00:09:28,359 --> 00:09:29,444
Beemo, what the heck?

193
00:09:29,736 --> 00:09:32,363
I am Football! And I am safe up here!

194
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:36,451
Come on, man, we're worried about you.
Come back inside.

195
00:09:37,077 --> 00:09:38,745
No, no, no, no, no! No!

196
00:09:39,329 --> 00:09:40,705
(PANTING)

197
00:09:44,626 --> 00:09:46,002
I'm safe up here.

198
00:09:46,628 --> 00:09:49,255
No reflections. Safe.

199
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:50,757
BEEMO: Football.

200
00:09:52,759 --> 00:09:53,760
(GASPS)

201
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:56,137
Dirt hole!

202
00:09:56,638 --> 00:09:57,889
Ahhh!

203
00:09:59,516 --> 00:10:01,017
(GRUNTS) Ahhh!

204
00:10:01,017 --> 00:10:02,268
(SCREAMS)

205
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:13,655
(GASPS)

206
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:16,116
Football?

207
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:20,286
(GASPS) Beemo, this place.
It's beautiful here.

208
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:22,914
- All my friends are here.
- (QUACKS)

209
00:10:23,289 --> 00:10:24,666
Carlos is here.

210
00:10:25,917 --> 00:10:27,001
It's all I ever wanted.

211
00:10:27,669 --> 00:10:28,670
Hmm.

212
00:10:29,379 --> 00:10:30,421
About what I did...

213
00:10:30,797 --> 00:10:33,049
It's okay. I know why you did it.

214
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:35,176
I didn't like your bathroom much, either.

215
00:10:35,677 --> 00:10:37,637
There is no beauty in the bathroom.

216
00:10:38,513 --> 00:10:39,806
Will you still visit me?

217
00:10:40,056 --> 00:10:43,059
Yes, Football, because I love you.

218
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,811
I love you, Beemo.

219
00:10:46,187 --> 00:10:47,188
(QUACKS)

220
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:54,779
Beemo! You okay?

221
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:57,448
Oh, Finn and Jake! I am back!

222
00:10:57,699 --> 00:10:59,826
I am back! I'm really back! (LAUGHS)

223
00:11:00,034 --> 00:11:01,161
Oh!

224
00:11:01,703 --> 00:11:03,705
Put that traffic cone back
on your head, young man.

225
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:05,957
(CHUCKLING) Yes, I'd love to!

226
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:08,334
I've missed my traffic cone so much!

227
00:11:08,418 --> 00:11:09,836
(GIGGLES)

228
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:12,964
Hooray!

229
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:18,303
Come along with me

230
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:22,849
And the butterflies and bees

231
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:28,313
This party is so crazy!

